            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Can confirm that `au! nvim.swapfile` works for me instead, phew! This is a breaking change for users and I still can’t find it in the news. Thankfully it causes a startup Error so that users are aware of the problem. However, there is no searchable `:help` for the renaming of `nvim_swapfile`. Although `nvim.swapfile` is mentioned in `default_autocmds`, many users may not notice the subtle change of punctuation which is not mentioned in the help either, so it is confounding.",
